"Abstract The law firm, Cameron, Markby Hewitt together with management consultants Copper & Lybrand and a consortium of law firms around Europe recently completed a study relating to the harmonization of information security laws in the EC for DG-XIII of the European Commission. The study was part of the Commission's continuing security investigations programme — INFOSEC '92 and now, INFOSEC '93. Both programmes derive from a March 1992 Council Decision (92/242/EEC) which requires the Commission to prepare an Action Plan to develop strategies to protect information from accidental and deliberate threats. Wendy London reports."
